text: What makes Toxic beloved is his believability: there's no affect, no hyperbole, no trite, no overkill. He's a technical rapper and that doesn't get the respect it deserves because of all the sheng and the background of his music. There's no really magic formula when it comes to believability: either you convey your reality, however imagined, or lived, with skills or you rap endless nonsense like some rappers we all know.
